\par\plain {Eddie sat on the edge of his bed, the warm glow of his bedside lamp casting a gentle light over his room. Outside, rain drummed softly against the window. Filling the night with a steady, soothing rhythm. He held the now-crinkled envelope from Edenfield University. Still in disbelief that its contents had changed his life just one morning.}
\par\plain {His fingers brushed against a hidden weight as he turned the envelope over. Curious, he returned to the envelope and pulled out a second, more personal-looking letter. His brows knitted together as he carefully unfolded it. Recognising the neat script of Emma Somers.}
\par\plain {He read quietly, the room settling into a hushed stillness as her words sank in:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 "Dear Edward,}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 First and foremost, congratulations on your acceptance to Edenfield University. You have earned it through merit, hard work, and courage. I am writing to tell you how genuinely pleased I am for you and to provide details for your departure to Edenfield next month. I hope you\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92re as ready for this journey as I know you will be.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 I owe you an apology for the last few weeks. You\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92ve no doubt sensed my hesitation\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 my doubt, even. Know that it was never personal, only the weight of the expectations placed upon this institution. Yet you exceeded every challenge put before you, and I can confidently say you belong in Edenfield.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 You will be assigned a place in the Sage\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s Institute dormitory. A modest allowance will be provided to support you as you settle}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 I wish you all the best in what\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s to come, and may this journey be everything you hope for. I believe you\u8217\'92ll find your way to greatness in the path that lies ahead._}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 With warm regards,}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1\i1 Emma Somers}{\f0\fs24\i1 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93}
\par\plain {Eddie stared at the letter, a quiet pride settling as he read her words. He could feel a renewed determination stirring within him. This wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t just a new beginning but an acknowledgement of his efforts and worth. Her words held a weight he hadn\u8217\'92t expected, and for a moment, the self-doubt that had haunted him seemed to fade.}
\par\plain {Eddie lay back on his bed, staring at the ceiling as memories washed over him. Each was like a page-turning in a story he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d only begun to understand. He thought of the long days spent poring over books with Catherine. The whispered doubts that had crept into his mind as he\u8217\'92d struggled to understand alchemical principles. The seemingly endless nights when he\u8217\'92d questioned if magic was even his path to follow. How many times had he stared into his potions and incantations? Feeling that, somehow, magic itself was just beyond his reach?}
\par\plain {He could remember moments of frustration. Those days when the spells didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t work, when his concoctions fizzled, when he felt like he was forcing something that didn\u8217\'92t belong to him. And yet, he could remember the joy when things did click. When he created something marvellous, even if small. But until today, he\u8217\'92d always wondered whether he deserved any of it.}
\par\plain {Reading Emma\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s letter, he felt a new sense of validation. Her faith in him felt like more than just an endorsement for Edenfield. It was the first solid proof that others saw in him what he\u8217\'92d so often struggled to see in himself. For the first time, he felt the quiet weight of the responsibility that came with magic\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 not a burden, but a privilege he had earned.}
\par\plain {Closing Emma\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s letter, Eddie took a deep breath, letting a feeling of calm settle over him. The journey ahead was daunting, yes, but he was also ready for it. Edenfield would be another chapter\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a chance to discover the magic in the world and the strength within himself. He\u8217\'92d earned his place, and for the first time, he truly believed it.}
\par\plain {The rain continued its soft murmur outside, and as Eddie drifted into sleep, a sense of peace filled him, as though all his past struggles had prepared him for the journey ahead. }
